This paper discusses the creation and use of benchmarks for AI Planning, which falls under the category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper specifically focuses on the domains used in the International Planning Competition (IPC), which is a subfield of AI Planning and falls under the category of Programming Languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the use of heuristics and empirical results, which are relevant to Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the engineering and organization of the benchmarks, which is relevant to Software Engineering (cs.SE).
